    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think @Carreau is right - it's calculating the div width based on the width of the content, then adding a scrollbar, which subtracts from the actual available width. If only browsers were good at math :(.  I think fixing that calculation to add enough horizontal space for the scrollbar should solve the issue. I expect that's stupidly complicated compared to how it should be, so maybe setting min-width to 80 chars + scrollbar width is the way to go.\n"
